{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_56","type":"command_execution","command":"/usr/bin/bash -lc \"rg -n \\\"generateMetadata|agentAllowedPackages|natively-collected|dynamic-access-coverage\\\" -g '*.gradle' -g '*.gradle.kts' -g '*.groovy' -g '*.java' -g '*.md' .\"","aggregated_output":"./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:42:If you already have the test project structure in this repository and need to generate or regenerate metadata, use the `generateMetadata` task:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:45:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:48:To change the user-code-filter used during collection, pass `--agentAllowedPackages` with a comma-separated list of packages or `fromJar` to derive package roots from the resolved library JAR:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:51:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:52:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=com.example.pkg,org.acme.lib\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:192:Generates metadata for a single library coordinate. If `agentAllowedPackages` is provided, a new user-code-filter.json will be created or updated from those packages or from package roots derived from the resolved library JAR.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:195:- `agentAllowedPackages`: comma-separated package list, `fromJar`, or `-` for none\n./d